\\":\\\"Washington\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://www.indoordogpark.org/states/washington\\\"}]}\"}}],[\"$\",\"$L11\",null,{\"variant\":\"light\"}],[\"$\",\"$L24\",null,{}],[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"state-page-layout\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"state-hero-section\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell state-hero-shell\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"state-hero-copy\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-breadcrumbs\",\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"›\"}],[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/states\",\"children\":\"States\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"›\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"children\":\"Washington\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-eyebrow\",\"children\":\"Evergreen State Enrichment\"}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"children\":\"Dog Parks in Washington\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-description\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"p\",\"0\",{\"children\":[\"Washington State has earned its reputation as one of the most dog-friendly destinations in America, with Seattle consistently ranking among the top 5 cities for dog owners by WalletHub and Rover's annual surveys. The state's 200+ days of overcast weather hasn't deterred dog lovers—it's actually spurred innovation. The Puget Sound region pioneered the \\\"indoor dog park\\\" concept in the Pacific Northwest, with warehouse conversions in SODO and Ballard now serving thousands of members who refuse to let rain interrupt playtime. Marymoor Park in Redmond features a legendary 40-acre off-leash area that draws visitors from across the region every weekend.\"]}],[\"$\",\"p\",\"1\",{\"children\":[\"Beyond the Seattle metro, Washington offers remarkable diversity in dog-friendly spaces. The agricultural Yakima Valley and Spokane areas provide wide-open spaces with less crowding, while Olympic Peninsula trails welcome leashed hiking companions through temperate rainforests. The state's progressive pet culture is reflected in regulations—King County alone maintains 14 official off-leash areas with dedicated maintenance budgets. Our directory tracks over 130 verified locations statewide, from the premium indoor facilities of Bellevue to the rustic trails of Eastern Washington, all with current hours, amenity details, and community ratings from local dog owners.\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-cta-row\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/cities\",\"className\":\"hero-cta primary\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-map\"}],\"Browse cities\"]}],[\"$\",\"$L12\",null,{\"href\":\"/list-your-park\",\"className\":\"hero-cta ghost\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-plus-circle\"}],\"Submit a park\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-footnotes\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",\"Heavy focus on King County\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-arrow-repeat\"}],\" \",\"Heavy focus on King County\"]}],[\"$\",\"span\",\"Indoor rain-plans included\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"i\",null,{\"className\":\"bi bi-arrow-repeat\"}],\" \",\"Indoor rain-plans included\"]}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"state-hero-visual\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-image-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L25\",null,{\"src\":\"/images/states/washington/hero.webp\",\"alt\":\"Washington dog park landscape\",\"fill\":true,\"priority\":true,\"sizes\":\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 40vw\",\"style\":{\"objectFit\":\"cover\"},\"unoptimized\":true}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"hero-image-gradient\"}]]}]}]]}]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"state-section\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"section-shell\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"feature-grid\",\"children\":[[\"$L26\",\"$L27\"],[\"$L28\",\"$L29\"]]}]}]}],\